Use the standard library
This is how to triangle_area of a and b and c:
  Remember that s is quotient of sum of a and b and c and 2
  When a is at least sum of b and c, then:
    The answer is -1
  But, if not:
    When b is at least sum of a and c, then:
      The answer is -1
    But, if not:
      When c is at least sum of a and b, then:
        The answer is -1
      But, if not:
        Remember that area_squared is product of s and diff of s and a and diff of s and b and diff of s and c
        The answer is sqrt of area_squared
      End when
    End when
  End when
